"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-boxing-2024-0306-1436414-mcdonagh-moves-on-to-last-16-at-olympic-qualifiers\", \"text\": \"Martin McDonagh is into the last 16 of Olympic qualifiers in Italy after an impressive win over Turkish fighter Yusuf Acik on Wednesday.  Th U-22, senior and elite Irish champion won every round on the judges' scorecard, coming away with a unanimous victory that moves him to within two wins of securing his place at the Paris Games.  McDonagh's latest win comes after the Crumlin native defeated the experienced Ferely Ali Feliz of the Dominican Republic in the opening round on Sunday.  Ireland has eight boxers at the tournament, which is taking place at the E-Work Arena in Busto Arsizio, 25km north of Milan.  Should any reach the semi-finals, they will be guaranteed a place at the Paris Games.  Tokyo bronze medalistAidan Walshproduced a commanding performance on Tuesday to defeat UAE's Husain Alkandari in his first-round bout.  Daina Moorehouse (50kg), Jude Gallagher (57kg) and Kelyn Cassidy (80kg) have also racked up wins over the last two days.  Follow theRT\\u00c9 Sport WhatsApp channelfor the best news, interviews, analysis and features, as well as details of our sports coverage across all RT\\u00c9 platforms.    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"